<li><a href="http://www.russian-records.com/" class="external text" title="http://www.russian-records.com/" rel="nofollow">The Encyclopedia of Russian pre-Revolutionary Recordings</a> Discography and Forum dedicated to early Russian recordings</li>
<li><a href="http://vinylfanatics.com/" class="external text" title="http://vinylfanatics.com/" rel="nofollow">Vinylfanatics.com</a> Current news and reviews to do with Gramophone records. Also a forum.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.rfwilmut.clara.net/repro78/repro.html" class="external text" title="http://www.rfwilmut.clara.net/repro78/repro.html" rel="nofollow">Reproduction of 78&#160;rpm records</a> including equalization data for different makes of 78s and LPs.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.archive.org/details/CommandP1942" class="external text" title="http://www.archive.org/details/CommandP1942" rel="nofollow">The manufacturing and production of shellac records</a>. Educational video, 1942.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.archive.org/details/SoundAndTheS" class="external text" title="http://www.archive.org/details/SoundAndTheS" rel="nofollow">The manufacturing and production of vinyl records</a>. Educational video, 1956.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.archive.org/details/LivingSt1958" class="external text" title="http://www.archive.org/details/LivingSt1958" rel="nofollow">Introducing stereophonic phonograph records</a>. Educational video, 1958.</li>
<li><a href="http://pastthepages.ca/090128/arts1.html" class="external text" title="http://pastthepages.ca/090128/arts1.html" rel="nofollow">Forget CDs: a return to music's vinyl roots</a>. The Lance, Jan. 28, 2009.</li>
</ul>
